UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1533
1 acknowledge the life and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.; and
2 WHEREAS, in so doing, the members urge all Kentuckians to recommit
3 themselves to the lessons Dr. King preached about more than half a century ago;
4 NOW, THEREFORE,
5 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
6 Commonwealth of Kentucky:
7 Section 1. The members of the House of Representatives hereby honor the life
8 and legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., and urge all Kentuckians to shape their lives by
9 those holy tenets of kindness, peace, and equality.
10 Section 2. When the House of Representatives adjourns this day, it does so in
11 honor and loving memory of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.
12 Section 3. The Clerk of the House of Representatives is directed to transmit a
13 copy of this Resolution to Representative Lindsey Burke.
